#: changes.rst:169
msgid "Weblate 2026.6"
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:175
msgid ""
":doc:`/admin/announcements` can now also be managed via the :ref:`api` for "
"specific project languages."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:176
msgid ""
"Team memberships can now be limited to selected languages for per-user "
"translation permissions."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:177
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ":ref:`machine-translation`"
msgid "Added :ref:`cost estimates <cost-estimate>` to translation reports."
msgstr ":ref:`machine-translation`"

#: changes.rst:178
msgid ""
"Added optional :ref:`OpenTelemetry tracing <collecting-errors>` for backend "
"requests and tasks, and :ref:`Google Cloud Error Reporting <collecting-"
"errors>` for handled server errors."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:179
msgid ""
"Added :doc:`/admin/workspaces` to group related projects, with workspace "
"project listings, workspace-scoped teams and project creation permissions, "
"inherited workspace, project, and category defaults for selected component "
"settings, and billing details when available."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:183
msgid ""
"Docker containers can now configure :envvar:`WEBLATE_SAML_SECURITY_CONFIG` "
"to customize SAML security settings, and adjust :setting:`WEBLATE_FORMATS` "
"using :envvar:`WEBLATE_ADD_FORMATS` and :envvar:`WEBLATE_REMOVE_FORMATS`."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:184
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ":ref:`mt-google-translate-api-v3`"
msgid ""
"Improved performance of the :ref:`check-inconsistent` check on large "
"projects."
msgstr ":ref:`mt-google-translate-api-v3`"

#: changes.rst:185
msgid ""
"Translation flag fields now use a tag-based editor with autocompletion and "
"grouped suggestions for all known flags."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:186
msgid ""
":ref:`Contributor stats <stats>` now de-duplicate repeated work on the same "
"string by default, with an option to count all changes."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:187
msgid ""
":doc:`/admin/code-hosting` now documents HTTPS access-token URLs and "
"dedicated-user SSH URLs for accessing repositories, and :doc:`/admin/"
"continuous` now explains why squash merging Weblate conflict-resolution pull "
"requests can require a repository reset."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:188
msgid ""
":ref:`alerts` now include dismissible component diagnostics for community "
"localization."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:189
msgid ""
":ref:`screenshots` now support bulk assignment from search or image text "
"recognition results, make finding strings in uploaded images easier to "
"discover, show source string coverage counts, and include advanced listing "
"search."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:190
msgid ""
":ref:`sbom` release artifacts now include CISA 2025 document-level metadata."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:194
msgid ""
"Outbound URL validation now rejects additional non-public targets "
"(:cve:`2026-50127`, :ghsa:`vmfc-9982-2m45`)."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:195
msgid ""
"Project-language :doc:`/admin/announcements` no longer appear across the "
"whole project."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:196
msgid ""
"Hardened :http:post:`/api/screenshots/` access checks against private "
"project enumeration."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:197
msgid ""
"Registration-attempt account activity e-mails now link to password reset to "
"help users finish account setup."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:198
msgid ""
":ref:`invite-user` links now work for signed-in users whose account owns the "
"invited e-mail address."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:199
msgid ""
"Searching for strings with content changes without a recorded author now "
"supports ``changed_by:\"\"``, and combined change filters now apply to the "
"same change event."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:200
msgid ""
"Gitea and Forgejo pull requests no longer reconfigure existing fork remotes "
"to point to the source repository."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:201
msgid ""
"Project and category language translation sessions now keep strings grouped "
"by component priority and show component switch warnings reliably."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:202
msgid ""
"Engage page task links now stay centered and show the target translation "
"language."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:203
msgid ""
"Gettext POT update add-ons now rescan translations after committing updated "
"POT and PO files."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:204
msgid ""
"Git repositories now update branches correctly when the remote also has a "
"tag with the same name."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:205
msgid ""
"Conflicting repository setup alerts now allow same-branch direct pushes."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:206
msgid ""
"Obsolete cleanup schedules are now removed from Celery beat during upgrade."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:207
msgid ""
"Translation pages for workspace projects no longer crash when workspace "
"fields are deferred."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:213
msgid ""
"There is a change in :setting:`django:INSTALLED_APPS`; "
"``weblate.workspaces`` should be added."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:214
msgid "The database migrations might take longer on larger instances."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:220
msgid ""
"`All changes in detail <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/milestone/165?"
"closed=1>`__."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:223
msgid "Weblate 2026.5"
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:225
msgid "*Released on May 15th 2026.*"
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:229
msgid ""
"Added :ref:`mdx` support for translating Markdown text while preserving JSX "
"syntax, with :ref:`file_format_params` shared with :ref:`markdown` for line "
"wrapping, code blocks, front matter, and placeholder handling."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:230
msgid ""
"Added extended :ref:`LLM translation context <llm-translation-context>` for "
"automatic suggestions, covering string context, explanations, secondary-"
"language translations, plurals, failing checks, and placeholders."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:231
msgid ""
"Added a digest-only translation activity summary notification, "
"see :ref:`notifications`."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:232
msgid ""
":ref:`CSV <csv>` and :ref:`XLSX <xlsx>` downloads in :ref:`download` now "
"export plural strings as separate plural-form rows that can be imported back."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:233
msgid ""
"Added Gettext PO and POT :ref:`file_format_params` to control whether "
"Weblate updates the ``Language-Team``, ``Last-Translator``, ``X-Generator``, "
"and ``Report-Msgid-Bugs-To`` headers."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:234
msgid ""
"Added a :ref:`backup-management-command` to run configured backup services "
"synchronously."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:235
msgid ""
"The translation memory lookup API can now skip fuzzy matching with the "
"``exact`` query parameter."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:236
msgid ""
"Added :ref:`addon-weblate.cdn.files` to publish translation files to the "
"configured CDN."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:240
msgid ""
"Using DOS line endings can now be configured using the "
"``dos_eol`` :ref:`file_format_params`."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:241
msgid ""
":ref:`mt-openai` and :ref:`mt-alibaba` no longer require their vendor Python "
"SDKs."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:242
msgid ""
"Audited project and component setting changes are now recorded in history."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:243
msgid ""
"Gerrit review pushes now use :ref:`component-push_branch` as the target "
"branch."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:244
msgid ""
"Weblate now checks whether :setting:`CACHE_DIR` allows executing generated "
"helper files."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:245
msgid ""
"The :ref:`sbom` is now generated during release and published as a versioned "
"release asset instead of being stored in the source repository."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:246
msgid ""
"The translating page now separates screenshots from string information, "
"collapses rarely used string details, and groups glossary and screenshot "
"actions more consistently."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:247
msgid ""
"Project access management now paginates users and better explains site-wide "
"automatic team assignments."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:248
msgid ""
"Added provider-oriented code hosting documentation and Gettext-"
"style :ref:`plural-formula` guidance."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:249
msgid ""
"The Python wheel no longer ships source translation catalogs, test files, or "
"deployment example files, reducing the installed package size."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:250
msgid ""
"The engage page now highlights actionable translation task buckets for "
"newcomers."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:251
msgid ""
":ref:`RSS feeds <rss>` can now use the same filters as the changes browsing "
"page."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:252
msgid ""
":ref:`addon-weblate.gettext.django` now supports gettext PO files used as "
"templates when they are excluded by the language filter."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:253
msgid "Reworked :doc:`/security/threat-model` into a contract-style document."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:257
msgid ""
"Hardened search previews and :ref:`machine-translation` suggestion origins "
"against XSS, and stopped exposing database error details in upload failures "
"(:cve:`2026-45106` / :ghsa:`6wxc-8mgq-w26m`)."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:258
msgid ""
"Screenshot URL uploads, remote HTML extraction in :ref:`addon-"
"weblate.cdn.cdnjs`, and URL health-check redirects now reject internal or "
"non-public targets by default."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:259
msgid ""
"Gerrit review pushes now reject target branches containing push options, "
"track the target branch before invoking ``git-review``, and suggest short "
"branch names when full refs are supplied."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:260
msgid ""
"Category :doc:`/admin/announcements` no longer appear across the whole "
"project, and translation announcement deletion now honors language-scoped "
"permissions."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:261
msgid ""
"Merge request pushes now refresh stale fork remotes after changing "
"repository hosting."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:262
msgid ""
"Plural counts parsed from translation file headers are now bounded, and "
"plural formulas are rejected when they can evaluate outside the configured "
"plural form range."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:263
msgid ""
":ref:`project-api` expiring today now remain valid until the end of the day."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:264
msgid ""
"Malformed ALTCHA CAPTCHA submissions and repository URLs in webhook payloads "
"no longer cause server errors."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:265
msgid ""
":ref:`check-placeholders` now merges overlapping non-nested spans from "
"multiple flags."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:266
msgid ""
":ref:`backup` logs no longer include OpenSSH post-quantum key exchange "
"warnings from remote Borg connections."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:267
msgid ""
"Category repository paths are now handled more safely during cleanup and "
"moves."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:268
msgid ""
"Locked component pages now show an unsubscribe action after subscribing to "
"unlock notifications."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:269
msgid ""
":ref:`projectbackup` imports now restore in the background to avoid web "
"worker memory limits."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:273
msgid ""
"The ``dos-eol`` flag is no longer supported. Use the "
"``dos_eol`` :ref:`file_format_params` instead."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:274
msgid ""
"The registration CAPTCHA now uses the ALTCHA widget v3 protocol with "
"Argon2id proof-of-work."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:275
msgid ""
"The ``set_language_team`` project attribute has been replaced with the "
"``po_set_language_team`` file format parameter at the component level; "
"see :ref:`file_format_params`."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:276
msgid ""
"Weblate now uses calendar versioning for releases, see :ref:`release-cycle`."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:277
msgid ""
"Weblate now uses stricter dependency version constraints to better control "
"runtime environment."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:283
msgid ""
"The ``ALTCHA_MAX_NUMBER`` setting has been replaced "
"by :setting:`ALTCHA_COST`, :setting:`ALTCHA_MEMORY_COST`, "
"and :setting:`ALTCHA_PARALLELISM`; please adjust your settings accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:284
msgid ""
"The upgrading policy was changed, and upgrades are only supported from the "
"current or previous calendar year."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:285
msgid ""
"The ``COMMENT_CLEANUP_DAYS`` and ``SUGGESTION_CLEANUP_DAYS`` settings are "
"migrated once to site-wide :ref:`addon-weblate.removal.comments` "
"and :ref:`addon-weblate.removal.suggestions` add-ons; configure those add-"
"ons instead."
msgstr ""

#: changes.rst:291
msgid ""
"`All changes in detail <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/milestone/162?"
"closed=1>`__."
msgstr ""

