"name]`` with the human-readable rule name. Place the comment on the line "
"above the logical statement or block when that does not broaden the "
"suppression scope. Keep the comment inline when moving it would change the "
"scope, affect import sorting, or get between another tool's ``disable-next`` "
"comment and the code it targets."
msgstr ""

#: contributing/snippets/code-guide.rst:99
msgid ""
"The easiest approach to enforce all this is to install :program:`prek`. This "
"is a third-party reimplementation of the `pre-commit`_ tool used by Weblate. "
"It is included in the development dependencies declared "
"in :file:`pyproject.toml`, so installing those dependencies "
"makes :program:`prek` available."
