"Weblate permissions are application authorization, not a host sandbox. A "
"user granted VCS or project management permissions can intentionally "
"configure integrations within that role's power. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:631
msgid ""
"Webhook project matching and event parsing are not proof that the sender is "
"the legitimate forge when the integration does not authenticate the "
"delivery. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:634
msgid ""
"Translation checks detect common quality and format problems; they are not a "
"guarantee that translated strings are safe for every downstream renderer. "
"*(documented)* (source: :doc:`/user/checks`, :doc:`/security/localization-"
"threat`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:638
msgid ""
"BorgBackup encryption protects backup archives according to Borg's design; "
"Weblate does not add a separate cryptographic guarantee for Borg internals. "
"*(documented)* (source: :doc:`/admin/backup`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:641
msgid ""
"Rate limits reduce abuse of configured endpoints; they are not a guarantee "
"of availability under volumetric network attacks. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:644
msgid ""
"Well-known attack classes left partly or wholly to deployment or downstream "
"systems:"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:647
msgid ""
"Phishing and credential reuse are mitigated by authentication policy and "
"2FA, but Weblate cannot prevent users from disclosing credentials outside "
"the service. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:650
msgid ""
"Malicious translations can become XSS, format-string, command, or policy "
"problems in downstream applications that render them unsafely. "
"*(documented)* (source: :doc:`/security/localization-threat`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:652
msgid ""
"User-configurable outbound URL surfaces with documented private-target "
"restrictions reject internal or non-public targets by default; privileged "
"allowlists, proxies, and administrator-controlled configuration can "
"intentionally expand reachability. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:656
msgid ""
"Large repository histories, project scale, and background task volume "
"require deployment sizing and operational limits beyond Weblate's single-"
"input validation. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:661
msgid "Downstream responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:663
msgid ""
"Operators must deploy Weblate behind production-grade HTTPS with correct "
"proxy headers, hostnames, request-size limits, and secure-cookie behavior. "
"*(documented)* (source: :doc:`/admin/"
"install`, :setting:`ENABLE_HTTPS`, :setting:`ALLOWED_HOSTS`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:668
msgid ""
"Operators must assign teams, roles, project-scoped tokens, VCS credentials, "
"and project management permissions according to least privilege for their "
"organization. *(documented)* (source: :doc:`/admin/access`, :doc:`/api`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:672
msgid ""
"Operators exposing :ref:`hooks` must enable them only where needed and "
"provide deployment controls such as reverse-proxy rate limits, body-size "
"limits, monitoring, and optional source restrictions. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:676
msgid ""
"Operators must treat private-target allowlists, proxies, and privileged "
"outbound integration settings as intentional expansion of Weblate's default "
"network reachability limits. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:680
msgid ""
"Operators must keep backup import limits, API rate limits, and web rate "
"limits at values that match instance capacity and exposure. *(documented)* "
"(source: :doc:`/admin/config`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:683
msgid ""
"Operators must protect the Weblate data directory, configuration, backup "
"credentials, generated keys, database, datastore, and local shell access as "
"trusted infrastructure. *(documented)* (source: :doc:`/admin/backup`, :doc:`/"
"admin/install`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:688
msgid ""
"Downstream product teams must treat translated strings as untrusted content "
"in their own applications unless they have separately reviewed, escaped, and "
"validated them for the target renderer. *(documented)* (source: :doc:`/"
"security/localization-threat`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:693
msgid "Known misuse patterns"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:695
msgid ""
"Exposing webhook endpoints broadly, enabling project hooks, and relying on "
"webhook payloads as authenticated forge identity. This is unsafe because "
"some supported hooks are compatibility-oriented. Use deployment controls and "
"prefer authenticated integrations where available. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:699
msgid ""
"Granting project management, VCS, or access-management permissions to users "
"who are trusted only as translators. This is unsafe because those "
"permissions can affect repositories, credentials, or other users. Assign "
"narrower roles. *(documented)* (source: :doc:`/admin/access`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:703
msgid ""
"Sending sensitive source strings or private customer content to machine "
"translation providers without treating the provider as a data recipient. "
"This is unsafe because Weblate must transmit content to the configured "
"service, and the submitted content varies by provider and enabled feature. "
"Configure providers according to the data policy for the project. "
"*(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:708
msgid ""
"Importing project backups from untrusted sources as an administrative "
"convenience. This is unsafe because backups carry project metadata, "
"translation content, and repository state. Keep import limits enabled and "
"import only backups appropriate for the target instance. *(documented)* "
"(source: :doc:`/admin/backup`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:712
msgid ""
"Treating Weblate translation checks as proof that downstream applications "
"cannot be attacked through translated strings. This is unsafe because the "
"downstream renderer defines the final execution context. Review and escape "
"translations in the consuming application. *(documented)* (source: :doc:`/"
"security/localization-threat`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:718
msgid "Known non-findings"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:720
msgid ""
"A report that a reachable webhook can be called without forge authentication "
"and only triggers modeled update scheduling is not ``VALID`` by itself. It "
"is routed to ``VALID-HARDENING`` unless it bypasses documented limits, leaks "
"data, or causes effects beyond modeled scheduling. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:724
msgid ""
"A report that a project manager can change repository settings, VCS "
"credentials, or project configuration is not a vulnerability when the actor "
"has the documented permission for that action. *(documented)* "
"(source: :doc:`/admin/access`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:727
msgid ""
"A report that a project manager can configure Gerrit review push options is "
"not a vulnerability by itself. Gerrit interprets these options as the "
"configured Weblate Gerrit account and enforces Gerrit-side permissions. "
"*(documented)* (source: :ref:`component-push_branch`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:731
msgid ""
"A report against third-party add-on behavior is not a Weblate core "
"vulnerability unless the report shows Weblate's permission or installation "
"boundaries are bypassed. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:734
msgid ""
"A report that a malicious local operator can read configuration, run "
"management commands, or alter files is out of model because local operators "
"are trusted infrastructure. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:737
msgid ""
"A report that a downstream application renders a dangerous translation is "
"not a Weblate vulnerability unless Weblate itself violates a claimed "
"property while storing, checking, reviewing, or displaying that translation. "
"*(documented)* (source: :doc:`/security/localization-threat`)"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:743
msgid "Conditions that change this model"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:745
msgid ""
"Revise this model when Weblate adds a new public endpoint family, a new "
"authentication or token mode, a new default deployment mode, a new backup or "
"import format, a new VCS execution path, a new outbound integration class, a "
"new add-on execution capability, or a change to defaults for hooks, HTTPS, "
"rate limits, CSP, private-network access, or backup import limits. "
"*(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

#: security/threat-model.rst:751
msgid ""
"Revise this model when an unsupported component becomes supported product "
"surface, when a documented security property is removed or narrowed, or when "
"maintainers accept a vulnerability report that cannot be routed to a triage "
"disposition below. *(maintainer)*"
msgstr ""

